casebody.data:
Nathan DULL
v.
COMMISSIONER OF CORRECTION Supreme Court of Connecticut. Decided October 25, 2017

Robert L. O'Brien, assigned counsel, in support of the petition.

James M. Rails, assistant state's attorney, in opposition.

The plaintiffs petition for certification to appeal from the Appellate Court, 175 Conn.App. 250, 167 A.3d 466 (2017), is denied.
